<p>Test suites group related tests together and provide organization for your test output.</p>

<h3>Declaring a Suite</h3>

<p>Use <code>testSuite</code> to declare a named suite:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">namespace MyTests
open Crucible

testSuite "HTTP Client"

test "sends GET request" := do ...
test "sends POST request" := do ...

#generate_tests

end MyTests</code></pre>

<h3>Suite Names</h3>

<p>Suite names appear in test output and can be used for filtering:</p>

<pre><code>HTTP Client
───────────
[1/2]  sends GET request... ✓ (5ms)
[2/2]  sends POST request... ✓ (3ms)</code></pre>

<h3>Multiple Suites</h3>

<p>Define multiple suites in different namespaces:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">namespace Unit.Parser
open Crucible
testSuite "Parser Unit Tests"
-- tests...
#generate_tests
end Unit.Parser

namespace Integration.API
open Crucible
testSuite "API Integration Tests"
-- tests...
#generate_tests
end Integration.API</code></pre>

<h3>Suite Organization Patterns</h3>

<p><strong>By Component:</strong></p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">namespace Auth.Tests
testSuite "Authentication"
end Auth.Tests

namespace Database.Tests
testSuite "Database"
end Database.Tests</code></pre>

<p><strong>By Test Type:</strong></p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">namespace Unit
testSuite "Unit Tests"
end Unit

namespace Integration
testSuite "Integration Tests"
end Integration</code></pre>

<h3>Running Specific Suites</h3>

<p>Use CLI filtering to run specific suites:</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash"># Run suites containing "Parser"
lake test -- --suite Parser

# Run suites matching exactly
lake test -- --suite "HTTP Client" --exact</code></pre>

<h3>Test Discovery</h3>

<p>The <code>runAllSuites</code> macro automatically discovers all registered suites:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">def main : IO UInt32 := do
  runAllSuites  -- Finds and runs all suites</code></pre>

<p>Suites are registered when <code>testSuite "name"</code> is called in a namespace
and <code>#generate_tests</code> is called to collect tests.</p>

<h3>Importing Test Modules</h3>

<p>Ensure all test modules are imported in your test runner:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">import Crucible
import Tests.ParserTests
import Tests.DatabaseTests
import Tests.APITests

def main : IO UInt32 := do
  runAllSuites</code></pre>

<p>If a suite isn't running, check that its module is imported.</p>
